<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 29 at 9:24PM MDT until August 29 at 10:00PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Great Falls has issued a
* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Broadwater County in southwestern Montana...
South central Meagher County in central Montana...
Northeastern Gallatin County in south central Montana...
* Until 1000 PM MDT.
* At 924 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 19 miles east of Toston to 10 miles east of Bozeman,
moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
* Locations impacted include...
Ringling.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
